{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"da24f320-a201-4c5f-9cfc-6c453566f6e8","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n**Environment variables** to enable automatic crash dumps with your custom `createdump` path:\n\n```yaml\nenv:\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n    value: \"4\"                        # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n    value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"\n  - name: DOTNET_EnableCreatedumpOnCrash\n    value: \"1\"\n  - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics\n    value: \"1\"                        # optional: logs createdump activity\n  - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n    value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n```\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      # ... image, ports, etc.\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE          # required for createdump to attach\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi            # adjust based on expected dump size\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- `SYS_PTRACE` is mandatory — `createdump` uses `ptrace` to capture process memory.\n- `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` overrides the default lookup since yours isn't alongside the runtime.\n- Use a persistent volume instead of `emptyDir` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- The `%p` / `%t` tokens expand to PID and timestamp to avoid overwrites.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"27f7b331-2f27-478b-b0c4-0d1e054de797","outputTokens":466,"requestId":"680E:147218:C794FD:D4FF49:6A0B00A4"},"id":"6506e9eb-58c5-449a-b1bf-626bd73f4423","timestamp":"2026-05-18T12:06:06.426Z","parentId":"a41ec978-6da0-4a24-832d-efbe6bad6516"}
